I see it, therefore I believe it

From the sighting until now, where have the ten most famous debunked UFO images been shared around the World?

  • Among the top 100 results of Google.it and Google.com, which are the topics related to fake images phenomenon?
  • Which and how many times are the fake images related to relevant events of the last 6 years debunked on Google.com?
  • How has McDonald’s food in advertising been faked from 1997 until now in the American official website?
  • For what purpose are the ten most famous debunked UFO images still shared on the internet?
  • From the sighting until now, where have the ten most famous debunked UFO images been shared around the World?

Despite being declared false, UFO sightings images have been spread all over the world, in many countries that are geographically and culturally distant from each other. The map focuses especially on the actual distance that occur from the place of the sightings to the sharing country. In addition to the spreadability of the images, this last aspect defines the impact that images can have on the misinformation problem, which is not just national, but global.

Main Findings

In general, although the event takes place in a specific state, the countries that most share the image are not the adjacent ones, but the geographically opposite ones.

The image of Roswell is the one with more sharing feedback on the web. In fact, it is the image that touches all continents at least once. To be precise, it has been shared in 22 countries.

United States of America is the country with the highest rate of UFO sightings and at the same time the country with the highest number of sites talking about aliens.

Even though none of the sightings considered took place in Russia, it is the country in second place in terms of the number of sites that share and use debunked images.

In the African continent, compared to other countries, only Egypt is among the countries with the highest rate of sharing of fake images regarding sightings.
